records.nl_statement: Let $|G|=p q r$, where $p, q$ and $r$ are primes with $p<q<r$. Prove that $G$ has a normal Sylow subgroup for either $p, q$ or $r$.

  [Fintype G]  (hpqr : p < q ∧ q < r)

def isConvex (f : ℝ → ℝ) : Prop :=
  let a := (sInf {x | ∃ y, x < y ∧ f (x + y / 2) ≤ (f x + f y) / 2}) - 1
  let b := (sSup {x | ∃ y, x < y ∧ f (x + y / 2) ≤ (f x + f y) / 2}) + 1
  ContinuousOn f (Set.Ioo a b) ∧ ∀ x y : ℝ, x ∈ Set.Ioo a b → y ∈ Set.Ioo a b →
    f ((x + y) / 2) ≤ (f x + f y) / 2
